						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and the date is lost. It refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalladēva</hi> and states that the <hi rend="italic">Tantrapāḷa</hi> <hi rend="bold">Māchayya</hi> made a gift of land. Palaeographically the record belongs to the 11th century after Christ and hence it may be assigned to Jagadēkamalla-Jayasiṁha II.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
